cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) to enhance low-resolution radar acquisitions, which is a computer vision technique. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the trade-offs in radar design, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The use of GANs involves machine learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of micro-Doppler signatures, which is a signal processing technique and falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for circumventing radar design trade-offs, which involves optimization and falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
